All A&E departments and units/centres providing emergency care

This data is collected during a patient's time at hospital and is submitted to allow hospitals to be paid for the care they deliver.  Written notes by clinicians are coded up in a back office in hospitals (and often the medical secretary enter the written / recorded notes onto the system), so coding decisions are therefore taken at one step removed from the notes themselves.  
This clinical coded data is then used to populate the Commissioning Data Set used for payments.  Therefore the purpose of this data is both payment-related and clinical.

HES extracts are taken from on a monthly basis, at pre-arranged dates during the year. Each extract is cumulative and contains data submitted for the financial year so far, i.e. month 1 will only contain the data submitted with an activity date in April, but month 6 will contain data submitted with an activity date from April to September. One of the reasons for this is that additional data may be needed to update patient records from earlier in the year, e.g. an episode may potentially run for several months or an amendment may need to be made as clinical coding takes place on discharge.
